<subSubSection id="2AC02EB090A704C001CF50DE6ECD4BBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4A72BE419B67457A1E6CD4CF810265F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5154C6AC266D90DE280712533F85EB74" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Mexico (Guanajuato, Hidalgo, 
<normalizedToken id="0C15337D9D1C193593BB9ECC3997447E" originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
, Oaxaca, Puebla, 
<normalizedToken id="6C51F0FD9C0E25A6FEAF3A06DE6249F1" originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
), in xerophilous scrub, rarely pine/juniper woodland, on rocky, limestone soils, often near a drainage or in a wash or canyon, often on an eroded floodplain, sometimes within or at the sides of agricultural fields or pastures, 770-2500 m in elevation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A100EE9A6F744C2D9F558182F43F77DC" captionStart="Figure 79" captionStartId="F79" captionText="Figure 79. Map of geographic distribution of L. peduncularis based on herbarium specimen data." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.168.51904.figure79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/480091" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">79</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
